**
Go to portal and click on storage account

Click on create 

Enter resource group name

Enter storage account name  

choose storage keeping unit

click on review + create

**

CREATE STORAGE ACCOUNT BY POWERSHELL!!

open power shell connect to your account 

Enter command new-AzstorageAccount

Enter resource group name

Enter Storage account name 

Enter Sorage keeping unit type

Enter Location

DONE!!

**

FILE UPLOAD!!

Go to overview of Storage account

Click on upload 

choose file to upload

Create or choose a container 

tick on overwrite if existing

then click on upload.

**

TO CHECK THE UPLOADED FILE!!

CLick on storage browser 

Then click on blob containers

There click on the container you created to upload file 

Then it will show you the files.

Or you can download it

